import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_price = data['price'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_price, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Price: {median_price:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='engine_size', y='price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between car price and engine size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Engine Size')
    plt.ylabel('Car Price')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    car_make_counts = data['make'].value_counts()
    car_make_counts = car_make_counts.reset_index()
    car_make_counts.columns = ['make', 'count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='make', y='count', data=car_make_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common car make in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Car Make')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(title='Car Makes', labels=car_make_counts['make'].unique(), loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='mileage', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['mileage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['mileage'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of car mileage?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Car Mileage")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
